                            CAREER OPTIONS (TPP) SELECTION BY DCPD_ REMINDER 8_GOLDEN CHANCE 1_M.COM. BATCH 2027 PO

                            • 24 Nov 2025
                            • 13:11:07

                            Ref. No: CU/DCPD/25-26/O_251124-699                                                                                                                                              Date: 24-11-2025

                              

                                                                                       AY 25-26 Career Options (TPP) Selection by DCPD_ REMINDER 8

                                                                                            GOLDEN CHANCE 1_M.Com. Batch 2027 PO Notice No.- 40

                             

                                                                      Every small step taken with consistency builds the foundation for big achievements.

                            In reference to DCPD Career Planning Symposium Calendar- V2 (Ref No- CU/DCPD/25-26/O_250913-328), circulated on 13th Sep 25 and again shared on 23th Sep 25 and Reminder Notice (Ref. No: CU/DCPD/25-26/O_251027-519) shared on 27th  Oct 25, it is hereby again REMINDED to all M.Com Batch 2027 pass-out students to select the career option of their choice (as already communicated through DCPD Career Awareness Symposium scheduled on 10th Nov 2025). However, still, some of the students have not opted for any Career Option on UIMS till date.

                            To survive in an era of competition with the self and advancement in technology it is crucial for every individual to carve out a chunk of time and set a career goal at this stage itself to excel in the long run. The training and placement programme (TPP) is more than just preparation for a job interview; it is a gateway to unlocking a world of opportunities and shaping a future a student has always dreamt of.

                            Please note that no extensions will be given after 25th November 2025 to select any Career option, and students will not be able to select any career option on CUIMS post this date.

The training and placement programme (TPP) is more than just preparation for a job interview; it is a gateway to unlocking a world of opportunities and shaping a future a student has always dreamt of.

                            Please note that no extensions will be given after 25th November 2025 to select any Career option, and the students will not be able to select any career option on CUIMS post this date.

                            This is with reference to our earlier communications regarding your provisional admission at Chandigarh University.
                            It is to inform you that, we have noticed that you have not submitted the original or photocopy of the eligibility documents pertaining to the previous qualification. You are required to submit the same on PRIORITY, without fail.

                            "I undertake to submit the pending Eligibility Documents by (date).

                            Tech Fest Student Organizing Committee Participation

                            We are excited to announce that nominations are now open for the Student Committee of the Annual Tech Fest! This is your chance to become part of the dynamic team that drives one of the most anticipated and innovative events of the year.Joining the Tech Fest committee is more than just an opportunity to organize eventsits a platform to develop leadership, enhance teamwork, and gain real-world project management experience. Students selected will play key roles in planning, coordination, marketing, technical management, hospitality, sponsorships, and event executionexperiences that build strong portfolios and add immense value to personal and professional growth.

                            1. Provide details about accomplishments till date you may have achieved?
                            *Required
                            2. How do you think being on this committee will help you grow personally and professionally?
                            *Required
                            3. Which skills do you bring to the committee? (Examples: leadership, creativity, social media management, technical skills, logistics, communication)
                            *Required
                            4. Are you familiar with any technical tools or platforms (e.g., event management software, design tools, social media marketing)?
                            *Required
                            5. Propose one innovative idea to attract more participants or sponsors to the Tech Fest.
                            *Required
                            6. How do you handle working in a team with people who have different opinions?
                            *Required
                            7. If you could organize any tech activity without any budget constraints, what would it be?
                            *Required
                            8. Have you been part of any event organizing team before? If yes, describe your role and contribution.
                            *Required
                            9. Select the core Organizing role which you may wish to undertake along with preference number
                            10. Upload your updated resume. (if any)
